verses.verse: The LORD <S%H3068><s%> reigneth, <S%H4427><s%> he is clothed <S%H3847><s%> with majesty; <S%H1348><s%> the LORD <S%H3068><s%> is clothed <S%H3847><s%> with strength, <S%H5797><s%> wherewith he hath girded himself: <S%H247><s%> the world <S%H8398><s%> also <S%H637><s%> is established, <S%H3559><s%> that it cannot <S%H1077><s%> be moved. <S%H4131><s%>
Thy throne <S%H3678><s%> is established <S%H3559><s%> of old: <S%H4480><s%> <S%H227><s%> thou <S%H859><s%> art from everlasting. <S%H4480><s%> <S%H5769><s%>

The floods <S%H5104><s%> have lifted up, <S%H5375><s%> O LORD, <S%H3068><s%> the floods <S%H5104><s%> have lifted up <S%H5375><s%> their voice; <S%H6963><s%> the floods <S%H5104><s%> lift up <S%H5375><s%> their waves. <S%H1796><s%>

The LORD <S%H3068><s%> on high <S%H4791><s%> is mightier <S%H117><s%> than the noise <S%H4480><s%> <S%H6963><s%> of many <S%H7227><s%> waters, <S%H4325><s%> yea, than the mighty <S%H117><s%> waves <S%H4867><s%> of the sea. <S%H3220><s%>

Thy testimonies <S%H5713><s%> are very <S%H3966><s%> sure: <S%H539><s%> holiness <S%H6944><s%> becometh <S%H4998><s%> thine house, <S%H1004><s%> O LORD, <S%H3068><s%> forever. <S%H753><s%> <S%H3117><s%>
